        <Summary xml:lang="en">Implements boolean algebra in one module</Summary>
        <Description xml:lang="en">boolean.py is a small library implementing a boolean algebra. It defines two base elements, TRUE and FALSE, and a Symbol class that can take on one of these two values. Calculations are done in terms of AND, OR and NOT - other compositions like XOR and NAND are not implemented but can be emulated with AND or and NOT.
</Description>
